WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:13.200
So, I'm Deepsha Meghani and today my goal is to be able to answer what is DataViz Animation,

00:00:13.200 --> 00:00:14.440
Interactivity and Linking?

00:00:14.440 --> 00:00:18.680
How can you get started with it in your storytelling within Quarto itself?

00:00:18.680 --> 00:00:21.879
And finally, have fun while we're learning that together.

00:00:21.879 --> 00:00:25.559
So there are lots of amazing packages already that you might have heard of.

00:00:25.559 --> 00:00:28.000
Some I've listed, some I might have missed.

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:31.520
But for the length of this talk, I'm going to focus on Plotly and Crosstalk.

00:00:31.520 --> 00:00:35.240
But know that each of those packages have unique strength for the need that you're

00:00:35.240 --> 00:00:36.240
trying to solve.

00:00:36.240 --> 00:00:40.400
But first, I want to talk about Ted Lasso.

00:00:40.400 --> 00:00:46.080
Ted Lasso is a show on Apple TV, and Apple is not paying me to tell you that.

00:00:46.080 --> 00:00:51.680
But there is an American football coach that is invited to teach UK-Richmond soccer team,

00:00:51.680 --> 00:00:54.919
or as the rest of the world calls, real football.

00:00:54.919 --> 00:00:59.400
And in that, the captain is Roy Ken, sitting on the right-hand side, who absolutely loves

00:00:59.400 --> 00:01:00.400
to say the word...

00:01:00.400 --> 00:01:01.400
Sorry.

00:01:01.400 --> 00:01:02.400
Sorry.

00:01:02.400 --> 00:01:04.040
I'll try that again.

00:01:04.040 --> 00:01:07.879
He absolutely loves to say the word...

00:01:07.879 --> 00:01:10.440
Looks like their AI-powered bleeping is working really well.

00:01:10.440 --> 00:01:11.559
Great job, guys.

